# Snippet for your project's CLAUDE.md

The canonical snippet lives at [`bb-api-agent-snippet.md`](bb-api-agent-snippet.md) — copy its contents into your project's `CLAUDE.md` so AI agents (Cursor, Copilot, Claude Code via CLAUDE.md) know how to use bb-api.

Two faster routes for Claude Code users:

- **Rule** (auto-loaded, always in context): copy [`bb-api-rule.md`](bb-api-rule.md) to `.claude/rules/bb-api-rule.md`.
- **Skill** (lazy-loaded, called when needed): copy [`bb-api-skill/SKILL.md`](bb-api-skill/SKILL.md) to `.claude/skills/bb-api/SKILL.md`.

Or run one command from inside your project to do any combination automatically:

```bash
bb-api install-agent              # interactive
bb-api install-agent --claudemd   # writes/appends to CLAUDE.md
bb-api install-agent --agents     # writes/appends to AGENTS.md
bb-api install-agent --rule       # drops .claude/rules/bb-api-rule.md
bb-api install-agent --skill      # drops .claude/skills/bb-api/SKILL.md
bb-api install-agent --rule --skill --claudemd --agents   # all four
```

See `bb-api install-agent --help` for `--dry-run` / `--force` / `BB_API_REF` pinning.
